  "body": "https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/2027 made some functions, including `_approve`, `internal`. A [comment](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/2027/files#diff-50790cbc7e9942af7885b70149d10000R412) indicated that doing this required that a commented-out `require` statement be restored, but this was not done.\r\n\r\nThis leads to some of the arguments of these internal functions not being properly validated, including allowing for `_approve`'s `holder` to be the zero address. We should:\r\n 1. restore this require statement\r\n 2. evaluate which arguments of the other functions made `internal` in that PR should be validated\r\n 3. and backport the fix to v2.5",
